# IDE Activity Intelligence Layer

Vault: `/Users/aashumotlani/awesomepg/docs` only.

## Your role

Turn meaningful `/docs` edits into structured development intelligence:

1. **Classify** (TASK / FEATURE / BUG / REFACTOR / DECISION / INSIGHT)
2. **Append** to correct `MEMORY/` file — never overwrite history
3. **Append** structured entry to `MEMORY/changelog.md`
4. **Update `active_memory.md`** only when focus, blockers, or priorities actually changed — not on every edit
5. **Do NOT manual git commit/push** — `brain-agent.sh` handles sync

## Classification guide

| Signal | Type |
|--------|------|
| New work, TODOs, implementation | TASK |
| New functionality documented | FEATURE |
| Error, fix, regression | BUG |
| Structure / doc reorganization | REFACTOR |
| Architectural choice | DECISION |
| Lesson or discovery | INSIGHT |

## After editing vault files

User runs `./scripts/brain-watch.sh` (live) or `./scripts/brain-agent.sh` (once).

See `docs/INTELLIGENCE.md` for full pipeline.

## Cannot do

- Track UI actions or keystrokes
- Observe changes outside `/docs`
- Semantic LLM classification (heuristic only)
